<item>
            <title>[SPARK-40096] Finalize shuffle merge slow due to connection creation fails</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-40096</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;How to reproduce this issue&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Enable push based shuffle&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Remove some merger nodes before sending finalize RPCs&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Driver try to connect those merger shuffle services and send finalize RPC one by one, each connection creation will timeout after SPARK_NETWORK_IO_CONNECTIONCREATIONTIMEOUT_KEY (120s by default)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
We can send these RPCs in&#160;&lt;b&gt;shuffleMergeFinalizeScheduler&lt;/b&gt;&#160; thread pool and handle the connection creation exception&lt;/p&gt;</description>
